---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout title="API Reference">
  <h1>API Reference</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-slate-400">Automate your data pipelines with the Datanika REST API.</p>

  <h2>Authentication</h2>
  <p>All API requests require an API key in the <code>Authorization</code> header:</p>
  <pre><code set:html={`curl -H "Authorization: Bearer etf_your_api_key_here" \\
     https://app.datanika.io/api/v1/...`} /></pre>
  <p>Create API keys in <strong>Settings &rarr; API Keys</strong>. See <a href="/docs/api-keys">API Keys</a> for details.</p>

  <h2>Connections</h2>

  <h3>List connections</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`GET /api/v1/connections

# Response
{
  "items": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Production Postgres",
      "connection_type": "postgres",
      "created_at": "2026-03-01T10:00:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "name": "BigQuery Warehouse",
      "connection_type": "bigquery",
      "created_at": "2026-03-02T14:30:00Z"
    }
  ]
}`} /></pre>

  <h3>Get connection</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`GET /api/v1/connections/1

# Response
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Production Postgres",
  "connection_type": "postgres",
  "created_at": "2026-03-01T10:00:00Z"
}`} /></pre>
  <p>Connection credentials are never returned in API responses.</p>

  <h3>Create connection</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`POST /api/v1/connections
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Staging MySQL",
  "connection_type": "mysql",
  "config": {
    "host": "mysql.staging.internal",
    "port": 3306,
    "database": "app",
    "user": "readonly",
    "password": "secret"
  }
}

# Response: 201 Created
{
  "id": 3,
  "name": "Staging MySQL",
  "connection_type": "mysql",
  "created_at": "2026-03-25T12:00:00Z"
}`} /></pre>

  <h3>Delete connection</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`DELETE /api/v1/connections/3

# Response: 204 No Content`} /></pre>

  <h2>Uploads (Extract + Load)</h2>

  <h3>List uploads</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`GET /api/v1/uploads

# Response
{
  "items": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Load orders",
      "source_connection_id": 1,
      "destination_connection_id": 2,
      "status": "active",
      "created_at": "2026-03-10T08:00:00Z"
    }
  ]
}`} /></pre>

  <h3>Create upload</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`POST /api/v1/uploads
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Load customers",
  "source_connection_id": 1,
  "destination_connection_id": 2,
  "dlt_config": {
    "load_mode": "single_table",
    "table_name": "customers",
    "write_disposition": "replace",
    "schema_name": "raw"
  }
}

# Response: 201 Created
{
  "id": 2,
  "name": "Load customers",
  "status": "draft",
  "created_at": "2026-03-25T12:00:00Z"
}`} /></pre>

  <h2>Pipelines (dbt Orchestration)</h2>

  <h3>List pipelines</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`GET /api/v1/pipelines

# Response
{
  "items": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Build analytics",
      "command": "build",
      "destination_connection_id": 2,
      "status": "active",
      "created_at": "2026-03-15T09:00:00Z"
    }
  ]
}`} /></pre>

  <h3>Create pipeline</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`POST /api/v1/pipelines
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Run staging models",
  "destination_connection_id": 2,
  "command": "run",
  "models": [{"name": "staging"}]
}

# Response: 201 Created
{
  "id": 2,
  "name": "Run staging models",
  "command": "run",
  "status": "draft",
  "created_at": "2026-03-25T12:00:00Z"
}`} /></pre>

  <h2>Transformations (dbt SQL Models)</h2>

  <h3>List transformations</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`GET /api/v1/transformations

# Response
{
  "items": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "stg_orders",
      "materialization": "view",
      "schema_name": "staging",
      "created_at": "2026-03-12T11:00:00Z"
    }
  ]
}`} /></pre>

  <h3>Create transformation</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`POST /api/v1/transformations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "mart_revenue",
  "sql_body": "SELECT date_trunc('month', order_date) AS month, SUM(amount) AS revenue FROM {{ ref('stg_orders') }} GROUP BY 1",
  "materialization": "table",
  "schema_name": "marts"
}

# Response: 201 Created
{
  "id": 5,
  "name": "mart_revenue",
  "materialization": "table",
  "schema_name": "marts",
  "created_at": "2026-03-25T12:00:00Z"
}`} /></pre>

  <h2>Runs</h2>

  <h3>List runs</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`GET /api/v1/runs

# Filter by status
GET /api/v1/runs?status=running

# Filter by target
GET /api/v1/runs?target_type=upload&target_id=1

# Response
{
  "items": [
    {
      "id": 42,
      "target_type": "upload",
      "target_id": 1,
      "status": "success",
      "rows_loaded": 15420,
      "started_at": "2026-03-25T12:00:01Z",
      "finished_at": "2026-03-25T12:02:34Z"
    }
  ]
}`} /></pre>

  <h3>Get run details</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`GET /api/v1/runs/42

# Response
{
  "id": 42,
  "target_type": "upload",
  "target_id": 1,
  "status": "success",
  "rows_loaded": 15420,
  "started_at": "2026-03-25T12:00:01Z",
  "finished_at": "2026-03-25T12:02:34Z",
  "logs": "Loading table orders...\\nLoaded 15420 rows in 2m 33s"
}`} /></pre>

  <h3>Trigger a run</h3>
  <pre><code set:html={`POST /api/v1/runs
Content-Type: application/json

# Run an upload
{"target_type": "upload", "target_id": 1}

# Run a pipeline
{"target_type": "pipeline", "target_id": 1}

# Run a transformation
{"target_type": "transformation", "target_id": 5}

# Response: 201 Created
{
  "id": 43,
  "target_type": "upload",
  "target_id": 1,
  "status": "pending",
  "created_at": "2026-03-25T14:00:00Z"
}`} /></pre>

  <h2>Import Configuration</h2>
  <p>Bulk-create connections, uploads, pipelines, and transformations from a JSON file. See <a href="/docs/ai-import">Backup & Import</a> for the full format specification.</p>
  <pre><code set:html={`POST /api/v1/import
Content-Type: application/json

# Body: same JSON format as the import file
{
  "version": 2,
  "connections": [...],
  "uploads": [...],
  "pipelines": [...],
  "transformations": [...]
}

# Response
{
  "connections_imported": 2,
  "uploads_imported": 3,
  "pipelines_imported": 1,
  "transformations_imported": 4,
  "skipped": 0
}`} /></pre>

  <h2>Error Responses</h2>
  <pre><code set:html={`{
  "error": "Unauthorized",
  "detail": "Invalid or expired API key"
}`} /></pre>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>200</code></td><td>Success</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>201</code></td><td>Created</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>204</code></td><td>Deleted (no content)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>400</code></td><td>Invalid request (validation errors)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>401</code></td><td>Missing or invalid API key</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>403</code></td><td>Insufficient permissions (scope mismatch)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>404</code></td><td>Resource not found</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>500</code></td><td>Server error</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Scopes</h2>
  <p>API keys can be scoped to limit access. Keys with no scopes have full access.</p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Scope</th><th>Allows</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>connection:read</code></td><td>List and view connections</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>connection:write</code></td><td>Create, update, delete connections</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>upload:read</code></td><td>List and view uploads</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>upload:write</code></td><td>Create, update, delete uploads</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>pipeline:read</code></td><td>List and view pipelines</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>pipeline:write</code></td><td>Create, update, delete pipelines</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>transformation:read</code></td><td>List and view transformations</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>transformation:write</code></td><td>Create, update, delete transformations</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>run:read</code></td><td>List and view runs</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>run:execute</code></td><td>Trigger new runs</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>import</code></td><td>Import configurations from JSON</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
